  "text": "(1) the general element A in the pencil | − K E(3) | is a smooth, abelian surface isogenous to E × E, and the restriction of β : E(3) −→ E to A gives rise to a smooth, isotrivial elliptic fibration A −→ E. Moreover the pencil contains four singular elliptic scrolls A 1 , . . . , A 4 ; (2) any X ηi is a smooth bielliptic surface of type 6 (see Chapter VI of [CITATION_1] ). The restriction of β gives rise to a smooth, isotrivial elliptic fibration X ηi −→ E, whereas the pencil | − K E(3) | cuts out on X ηi an isotrivial pencil of elliptic curves with three triple fibres.",
